    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Wood</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 22, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> The opening of the campaign is attended
                            with some embarrassments which, in the excitement of the moment, are
                            likely to be exaggerated. The expedition of General Franklin to Sabine
                            Pass was only one of three designed to re-establish the national
                            authority in Texas. Its repulse may retard, but it is not thought that
                            it endangers, the success of the plan.</p>
                <p>Official despatches from the army of the Cumberland have been received of
                            a date so late as two o’clock p. m. of the 21st. They are inexplicit,
                            but the general effect is thought to justify the expectation of our
                            continuing to hold our important positions in Tennessee. Should any
                            later news be seasonably received I will communicate it by
                            telegraph.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bradford R. Wood</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Copenhagen.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
